cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper is about social network analysis and studying the evolution of nodes in networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a new distributed algorithm based on MapReduce methodology. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of a scalable algorithm for finding Epsilon Equitable Partition of a graph. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with partitioning actors into disjoint sets using a notion of equivalence which captures the structure of relationships among actors. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with analyzing social networks which are a type of network.
